<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Buhari-3-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1" alt="Why rehabilitation of IDPs demands urgency ― Buhari" class="amp-wp-295b586"> Nigeria’s President Muhammadu Buhari has said that rehabilitation of internally displaced persons (IDPs) in the country is imperative and urgent, to avert possible problems in the future. Mr Femi Adesina, the President’s spokesman, in a statement in Abuja, said the president spoke when he received in audience the President of the 74th United Nations General Assembly (UNGA), Nigeria’s Prof. Tijjani Muhammad-Bande, at the State House, Abuja, on Monday. The president said: “Most of the displaced children do not know their parents, or where they come from. Continue reading Why rehabilitation of IDPs demands urgency ― Buhari at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard